stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> Created : Initiate Reminder

    Created : Reminder record defined in CRM; associated with an entity (e.g., Lead, Contact, Opportunity).
    Created --> Pending : Save & Schedule

    Pending : Reminder is active but awaiting its scheduled trigger time.
    Pending --> Triggered : At Scheduled Time

    Triggered : Reminder's scheduled time has passed; it is now active for notification.
    Triggered --> Delivering : Initiate Notification
    Triggered --> Overdue : Not Delivered (Timeout)

    Delivering : System attempting to send notification to the user.
    Delivering --> Delivered : Notification Sent Successfully
    Delivering --> Failed_to_Deliver : Notification Delivery Failed

    Delivered : Notification successfully transmitted to the user.
    Delivered --> Acknowledged : User Views / Interacts
    Delivered --> Overdue : Not Acknowledged (Timeout)

    Acknowledged : User has seen, opened, or otherwise interacted with the notification.
    Acknowledged --> Completed : Mark as Done / Action Taken
    Acknowledged --> Snoozed : Postpone Reminder

    Snoozed : User temporarily deferred the reminder.
    Snoozed --> Pending : Reschedule to New Time

    Failed_to_Deliver : Notification could not be sent. Requires manual intervention or system retry.
    Failed_to_Deliver --> Overdue : No Resolution (Timeout)
    Failed_to_Deliver --> Archived : Irrecoverable Failure

    Overdue : Reminder was not completed/resolved within its grace period post-trigger. May trigger escalation rules.
    Overdue --> Completed : User Resolves Overdue
    Overdue --> Archived : System Auto-Archives After (Timeout)

    Completed : User has performed the required action for the reminder.
    Completed --> Archived : Store Historical Record

    Created --> Cancelled : User/System Cancels (Pre-Schedule)
    Pending --> Cancelled : User/System Cancels (Pre-Trigger)
    Triggered --> Cancelled : User/System Cancels (Post-Trigger, Pre-Completion)
    
    Cancelled : Reminder was explicitly stopped by the user or system.
    Cancelled --> Archived : Store Historical Record

    Archived : Final dormant state.

    stateDescriptions
        Created : Reminder record defined in CRM; associated with an entity (e.g., Lead, Contact, Opportunity, Task).
        Pending : Reminder is active but awaiting its scheduled trigger time.
        Triggered : Reminder's scheduled time has passed; it is now active for notification.
        Delivering : System attempting to push notification via configured channels (e.g., email, in-app, SMS).
        Delivered : Notification successfully transmitted to the user's device/inbox.
        Failed_to_Deliver : Notification delivery attempt failed (e.g., invalid email, unreachable device).
        Acknowledged : User has viewed, opened, or otherwise interacted with the notification.
        Completed : User has performed the required action and marked the reminder as done.
        Snoozed : User temporarily deferred the reminder; it will re-enter the 'Pending' state with a new schedule.
        Overdue : Reminder was not completed or resolved within its expected timeframe post-trigger.
        Cancelled : Reminder was explicitly stopped by the user or system before completion.
        Archived : Final dormant state. Reminder is no longer active and is stored for historical purposes.
    end stateDescriptions